The paper discusses the impact of transceiver front-end hardware imperfections on the spectrum sensing performance of cognitive radios. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), computer communication (cs.COM), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on wireless communication and cognitive radios, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant but less likely as they are broader in scope.
